rdf:Description.dc:title: RDA Timespan properties
rdf:Description.skos:note: Properties derived from RDA elements and relationship designators with the domain of RDA Timespan. Warning! This element set is under development as part of the RDA Toolkit Restructure and Redesign Project. The last stable version can be found in release v2.7.3 of RDA Vocabularies in the RDA Registry.

rdf:Description.reg:name: accessPointForTimespan
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has access point for timespan
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a timespan to an appellation of timespan in natural language that is taken from a vocabulary encoding scheme or is constructed using a string encoding scheme.
rdf:Description.rdakit:toolkitDefinition: An appellation of timespan in natural language that is taken from a vocabulary encoding scheme or is constructed using a string encoding scheme.

rdf:Description.reg:name: appellationOfTimespan
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has appellation of timespan
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a timespan to a nomen used within a given scheme or context to refer to a timespan.
rdf:Description.rdakit:toolkitDefinition: A nomen used within a given scheme or context to refer to a timespan.

rdf:Description.reg:name: authorizedAccessPointForTimespan
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has authorized access point for timespan

rdf:Description.rdakit:toolkitDefinition: An access point for timespan that is selected for preference in a specific vocabulary encoding scheme.
